  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Dry cough is the most common adverse reaction of angiotensin converting enzyme, including
      enalapril, in Chinese population. Clinical observations suggest that the incidence of
      ACEI-induced dry cough is different between Chinese and other racial groups, however, there
      is still lack of research data in Chinese. In this study, we will investigate whether there
      are specific genotypes which may predict the incidence of enalapril-induced dry cough in
      Chinese so as to provide a basis for developing guidelines on precise medication in enalapril
      therapy apply to Chinese population.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
